A micro blogging site, Twitter has unverified the account of Nigeria’s Vice President, Yemi Osinbajo @ProfOsinbajo. The account was blocked first before it was later restored without the verification badge.  Checks on the handle as of the time of filing this report revealed only one tweet, which were retweets of an N-Power animation on August 3rd. Osinbajo’s handle, which has been used to document his activities now has no history, photos or any semblance to the handle.  Also, his profile and header images have been removed. The media aide to Osinbajo, Laolu Akande, has not responded to a text message sent to him as of the time of filing this report Kannywood Verified: Adam Zango joins Ali Nuhu, Rahama Sadau, Hadiza Gabon, others Boko Haram launches fresh online campaign, opens Twitter account Obasanjo demands AIT's apology, retraction on purported meeting with Osinbajo, Amaechi Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin